cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with unsupervised learning of identity-discriminative visual features, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves utilizing weak supervision to address visual discrepancy caused by different states, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on person re-identification and pose-invariant face recognition, which are sub-fields of multimedia (cs.MM) and computer security (cs.CR), respectively.
